The course offers insights into cultural experience and the variety of opportunities to study it. The course includes lectures and seminars, excursions and visits to museums (to get acquainted with the possibilities of mediating cultural phenomena) as well as independent work under the guidance of lecturers.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to introduce the ways ethnologists and folklorists observe and study culture through cultural experience.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course, student is familiar with the techniques ethnologists and folklorists use to gain access to cultural experience of individuals and small groups.
